# criteria.md — example scaffold for job-scanner

# HOW TO USE
#
#   cp criteria.md.example criteria.md
#
# Then edit the copy (criteria.md is .gitignore-safe by convention —
# your preferences shouldn't live in source control).
#
# The `job-scanner` preset reads this file automatically and uses
# it to score listings 1-10 before writing a ranked report. The
# more specific you are here, the better the scoring.


## Role

- Target roles: <e.g., SWE intern, data analyst intern, ML engineer>
- Seniority: <entry / intern / new-grad / mid-level / senior>
- Must-have skills: <e.g., Python, SQL, Go, React>
- Nice-to-have skills: <e.g., Kubernetes, TypeScript, Rust>


## Location + logistics

- Work arrangement: <remote / hybrid / in-office>
- Acceptable regions: <e.g., US Pacific NW, EU, anywhere>
- Timezone overlap needed: <e.g., must include 9am-12pm PT>
- Relocation: <yes / no / only for <city>>
- Start date / duration: <e.g., Summer 2026, ~12 weeks>


## Compensation

- Minimum salary: <$X or "no preference">
- Equity: <required / nice-to-have / no preference>
- Benefits that matter: <e.g., health insurance, 401k match, learning stipend>


## Dealbreakers  (score 1 automatically if any apply)

- Unpaid or "equity only"
- On-call rotation
- Requires security clearance I don't have
- Customer-facing sales role
- <add your own>


## Preferences  (nice-to-have signals)

- Small team (<50 people)
- Open-source or public work as part of the role
- Documented engineering practices (code review, testing)
- Clear promotion path
- <add your own>
